{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2018}} '''Alison Smith''' (born August 22, 1954) is a Canadian television and radio journalist and anchor. She graduated in 1972 from [[Southern Okanagan Secondary School]] in nearby [[Oliver, British Columbia|Oliver]], where her father Bruce was a guidance counsellor. She studied at the [[University of British Columbia]] in [[Vancouver]] and [[Ryerson University]] in [[Toronto]].
By 1982, Smith was working as a reporter in Toronto. From 2005 to 2009, Smith was [[CBC Television]]'s [[Washington, DC|Washington]] correspondent, succeeding [[David Halton]]. Prior to her Washington assignment, she was the host of the network's morning show: ''[[CBC News: Morning]]'', and she was also the anchor for ''[[CBC News: The National|The National]]'' from 1992 to 1995 when the program aired only on [[CBC Newsworld]] during which period ''[[CBC Prime Time News]]'' was CBC's flagship news show. Smith was also one of the first anchors for CBC Newsworld on the program ''This Day''.
On September 28, 2009, Smith became anchor of [[CBC Radio One]]'s ''[[The World at Six]]''.<ref>[https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/article/644546 "Alison Smith to join World at Six newscast"]. ''[[Toronto Star]]'', June 2, 2009.</ref> On May 8, 2014, Smith announced her retirement from CBC.<ref>{{cite news|title=Alison Smith latest CBC journalist to announce retirement|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2014/05/08/alison_smith_latest_cbc_journalist_to_announce_retirement.html|accessdate=May 8, 2014|newspaper=Toronto Star|date=May 8, 2014}}</ref> Smith's last day as anchor on ''The World at Six'' was June 26, 2014.<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/news/alison-smith-longtime-journalist-leaves-cbc-this-week-1.2688300 "Alison Smith, longtime journalist, leaves CBC this week"]. ''[[CBC News]]'', June 26, 2014.</ref> In 2016, she joined [[CPAC (TV channel)|CPAC]] as host of a new weekly series on international affairs.<ref>[http://www.broadcastermagazine.com/acquisition/cpac-unveils-new-look-welcomes-alison-smith/1004124419/ "CPAC Unveils New Look and Welcomes Alison Smith"]. ''Broadcaster'', November 16, 2016.</ref>
